{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-09-13","name":"Walter Kettins","nameForms":[{"lang":"und","fullText":"Walter Kettins","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Walter"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"Kettins"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"gender":"Male","lifespan":"1140–1190","fullLifespan":"abt 1140–1190","birthDate":"+1140","birthPlace":{"address":"Scotland","geo":{"latitude":56.81674,"longitude":-4.18396,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1190","deathPlace":{"address":"Angus, Scotland","geo":{"latitude":56.67,"longitude":-2.917,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"Biography\nWalter was born in the first half of the twelfth century.\n\nHe gained or inherited the lands of Kettins in Strathmore.\n\nWalter appears to have had sons:\n\nMalcolm of Kettins\nJohn of Kettins\nWilliam of Kettins\nAn agreement was reached between Durham Priory and Croyland Abbey at Stirling in 1167, in the presence of William, king of Scots, Richard, bishop of St Andrews, Ingram, bishop of Glasgow, Geoffrey, abbot of Dunfermline, William, abbot of Melrose, Earl Waltheof, Nicholas the chancellor, Richard the chaplain, David Olifard and others, concerning the villa and church of Edrom (BWK) whereby the abbot of Croyland renounced all claims to Edrom in Berwickshire and the prior of Durham agreed to pay 9 marks ‘in pennies’ at the church of St Leonard in Stamford, 60 shillings (£3) on St Agatha’s Day and the other 60 shillings on St Oswald’s Day. Walter of Kettins was among those witnesses to the document.Raine, North Durham, App., no. 642\n\nSources\nSource will be added by Jack Blair by 2 Dec 2021.","events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1140","date":"abt 1140","place":"Scotland"},{"name":"Marriage","sources":"0","year":"1185","date":"before 1185","place":"Europe","type":"Spousal","age":"44","id":"GKSS-WRZ"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1185","date":"about 1185","place":"K